class Solution {
public:
    int strStr(string haystack, string needle) {
        int n=haystack.length();
        int m=needle.length();
        for(int i=0;i<=n-m;i++){
            int j=0;
            while(j<m && haystack[i+j]==needle[j]){
                j++;
            }
            if(j==m) return i;
        }
        return -1;
    }
};

Steps:
Loop through haystack from 0 → n-m
For each index i, check:
Does substring starting at i match needle?
If match → return i
If no match found → return -1

⏱ Time Complexity:
Worst case: O(n × m)
(where n = haystack.length, m = needle.length)
